a. Ensure that cash advances shall only be given for a legally authorized specific purpose and adequately supported with relevant supporting documents;

b. Revisit the provision on supporting documents on the liquidation of cash advances as cited in COA Circular 2012-001, for the documentary requirements and , Sections 48 (l) and (m) of COA Circular No. 92-382 and adhere thereto;

c. Stop granting additional cash advances to officials and employees until the previous ones have been liquidated and/or settled; and

d. Submit the lacking documents noted in the observation and henceforth, faithfully adhere to all laws and regulations applicable to the financial transaction.

a. To enjoin the Municipal Development Investment Program (MDIP) Committee to revisit the project screening and prioritization criteria used in ranking and approving proposed projects for funding under 20% LDF to ensure that plans and budget adhere to the applicable laws, rules and regulations;

b. To direct the Departments involved in the formulation of plans budget under 20% LDF to provide for substantive and comprehensive inputs;

c. To provide for justification and/or legal bases on charging Personal Services expenditures and equipment rental for properties owned by the LGU in the 20% Development Fund. Henceforth, ensure that projects to be funded by LDF shall take the nature of investment or capital expenditures;

d. For the Municipal Engineering Office to review its current manpower complement vis a vis personnel workload and make a proposal to HRMDO for the required manpower to address such deficiencies and ensure an effective and timely implementation of infrastructure projects;

e. To direct the implementing departments to execute without delay and optimally utilize the 20% Development Fund to help achieve the desirable socio-economic development and environmental management outcomes of the LGU.

We recommend the following:
a. Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to locate documents pertinent to the LGU properties preparatory to the conduct of the mandatory physical inventory;
b. Submit a complete Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) to the Accounting Office for reconciliation with the latter's ledger cards;
c. Require the Accounting and GSO to maintain ledger and property cards as control records to facilitate the regular reconciliation of records; and
d. Require the General Service Office to maintain property stock cards for every acquisition indicating therein the complete description and specification of each property.
e. Make appropriate and necessary adjustments in the books of accounts.

